==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Glowworm
<hw>Glow"worm`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A coleopterous insect of the genus <gen>Lampyris</gen>; esp., the
wingless females and larv⟦ae⟧ of the two European species (<spn>L.
noctiluca</spn>, and <spn>L. splendidula</spn>), which emit light from
some of the abdominal segments.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Like a <qex>glowworm</qex> in the night,⟦br⟧
The which hath fire in darkness, none in light.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The male is winged, and is supposed to be attracted by
the light of the female. In America, the luminous larv⟦ae⟧ of several
species of fireflies and fire beetles are called <xex>glowworms</xex>.
Both sexes of these are winged when mature. See
<er>Firefly</er>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gloxinia</ent>⟦br⟧
